<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<body>
	<style>
	.font_1 {
		background-color: black;
		color: yellow;
		font-size: large;
	}
	.font_2 {
		background-color: darkblue;
		color: white;
		font-size: medium;
	}
	.Me_style {
		background-color: indigo;
		color: hotpink;
		text-decoration: underline;
		font-size: medium;
	}
	</style>
	<h2 class="font_1">This h2 element is styled per class attribute font_1</h2>
	<h3 class="font_2">This h3 element is styled per class attribute font_2</h3>
	<h4 class="font_1">Even thoigh this is  an h4 element, it is styled the same
	as the h2 element because we pointed to the class attribute font_1</h4>
	<p class="Me_style">This element was styled by me. We are practicing class attributes
	and styling them through the class attributes.
	</body>
</html>